            <thetext>The checkboxes and radiobuttons in Webkit browsers like safari and chrome are placed to close and slightly to low related to their labels.

The bug is simply reproducable in the demo browser for qooxdoo 0.7.x:

http://demo.qooxdoo.org/0.7.4/demobrowser/#example~CheckBox_1.html
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/0.7.4/demobrowser/#example~RadioButton_1.html

This is for Safari 3.2, Safari 4 and Chrome 2 under Windows Vista.

The problem is the default margin of the radiobox and the checkbox.

A patch is attached which removes the default margin as it is done for gecko based browsers.</thetext>
